{{Redirect3|Wyverns guide|For strategies on killing [[Skeletal Wyvern]]s, see [[Skeletal Wyvern/Strategies]]}} '''Note:''' All [[Fossil Island wyvern]]s may be killed in this same fashion regardless. However, the lower-tier [[Spitting Wyvern|spitting]], [[Taloned Wyvern|talon]] and [[long-tailed wyvern]]s require 66 [[Slayer]].
[[Ancient Wyvern]]s are the strongest species of [[Wyvern]]. They possess very high [[Defence]], [[Attack]], and [[Hitpoints]], thus making them very powerful foes. Like other Wyverns, they require an [[elemental shield|elemental]], [[mind shield|mind]], [[dragonfire ward]], [[dragonfire shield|dragonfire]],  or [[ancient wyvern shield]] to be equipped in order to be slain, or the player will suffer devastating damage from their unique icy breath. The [[ancient wyvern shield]] is the only shield that will grant immunity against the freezing effect from a wyvern's icy breath.

Note that after [[Bone Voyage]], a [[Slayer]] level of 82 is required in order to deal damage to Ancient Wyverns (not withstanding the effects of a [[poisoned]] weapon). Otherwise, eating a [[wild pie]] at 77 Slayer will do, though kills will be extremely long.

Quick travel tip is to use the [[Digsite pendant]], which should be used on the strange machine at the [[House on the Hill]], to teleport directly to [[Fossil Island]]. Should players already have unlocked the teleport, they may use a [[mounted digsite pendant]] within their [[Portal Nexus]] room instead if they have one. Run south-east to the [[Wyvern Cave|cave]] entrance. For Slayer tasks, you can use the [[Mycelium Transportation System|Magic Mushtree]] adjacent to the House on the Hill teleport location to appear just north of the task-only Wyvern Cave under the Mushroom Meadow. Alternatively, the player can teleport to the [[Digsite]], use the [[barge]], and run east past the bank and then south-east into the cave.

